POUND: A NORMAL-type attack. Slightly stronger than TACKLE. Many Pokémon know this move.
KARATE_CHOP: A Normal-type attack. Often turns into a critical hit and inflicts double the damage.
DOUBLESLAP: Although each slap is weak, this attack hits the target two to five times in succession.
COMET_PUNCH: Although each slap is weak, this attack hits the target two to five times in succession.
MEGA_PUNCH: A Normal-type attack move. It is highly accurate and relatively powerful.
PAY_DAY: A move that also nets money at the end of battle. How much depends on the attack frequency and level.
FIRE_PUNCH: A special Fire-type attack. Has a one-in-ten chance of inflicting a burn on the target.
ICE_PUNCH: A special Ice-type attack. Has a one-in-ten chance of freezing the target.
THUNDERPUNCH: A special Electric-type attack. Has a one-in-ten chance of paralyzing the target.
SCRATCH: A Normal-type attack. Sharp claws are used to inflict damage on the target.
VICEGRIP: A Normal-type attack used only by Pokémon with pincers. The target is gripped and injured.
GUILLOTINE: A single-hit knockout attack. Learned only by Pokémon that have large pincers.
RAZOR_WIND: A two-turn attack with the wind attack in the second turn. Learned by many Flying-type Pokémon.
SWORDS_DANCE: A special move that greatly boosts the user's Attack power. Can normally be used up to three times.
CUT: A Normal-type attack. Also used for cutting small bushes to open new paths.
GUST: A Normal-type attack used by bird Pokémon. A powerful wind is generated by flapping wings.
WING_ATTACK: A Flying-type attack. The attacking Pokémon spreads its wings and charges at the target.
WHIRLWIND: Generates a powerful wind that blows away wild Pokémon. Useful in the wild only.
FLY: The Pokémon flies high, then strikes in the next turn. Used for flying to places already visited.
BIND: Traps and squeezes the target over several turns. The target cannot move while under attack.
SLAM: A Normal-type attack move. The attacker uses an appendage (e.g. tail) to slam the target hard.
VINE_WHIP: A Grass-type attack. The Pokémon uses its cruel whips to strike the opponent.
STOMP: A Normal-type attack. Has a one-in-three chance of making the target flinch if it connects.
DOUBLE_KICK: A Fighting-type attack. As the name implies, it is actually two quick kicks in succession.
MEGA_KICK: A Normal-type attack. Out of all the Pokémon kicking attacks, this is the strongest.
JUMP_KICK: A forceful Fighting-type attack. If it misses, however, the attacker gets hurt.
ROLLING_KICK: A sharp Fighting-type attack. Has a one-in-three chance of making the target flinch if it connects.
SAND_ATTACK: An attack in which sand is used to blind the target and reduce its attack accuracy.
HEADBUTT: A Normal-type attack. Has a one-in-three chance of making the target flinch if it connects.
HORN_ATTACK: A Normal-type attack. A sharp horn is driven hard into the target to inflict damage.
FURY_ATTACK: A Normal-type attack. The Pokémon rapidly jabs at its opponent several times.
HORN_DRILL: A single-hit knockout attack. Learned only by Pokémon with a horn or horns.
TACKLE: A Normal-type attack. Many Pokémon know this attack right from the start.
BODY_SLAM: A Normal-type attack. Has a one-in-three chance of paralyzing the target if it connects.
WRAP: Traps and squeezes the target over two to five turns. The target cannot move while under attack.
TAKE_DOWN: A charging attack. One quarter of the damage it inflicts comes back to hurt the attacker.
THRASH: An attack that lasts two to three turns. Afterwards, the attacker becomes confused.
DOUBLE_EDGE: A charging tackle attack. One quarter of the damage it inflicts comes back to hurt the attacker.
TAIL_WHIP: A move that lower the target's Defense. Useful against tough, armored Pokémon.
POISON_STING: A Poison-type attack. Has a one-in-five chance of leaving the target with the lingering effects of poison.
TWINEEDLE: An attack that strikes twice. The target may occasionally become poisoned.
PIN_MISSILE: An attack that fires many needle-like projectiles from the body. Strikes several times.
LEER: A technique that lowers the target's Defense. Useful against tough, armored Pokémon.
BITE: A bite made using sharp fangs. This may cause the opponent to flinch, and it might not attack.
GROWL: A technique that lowers the target's Attack power. Can normally be used up to 6 times.
ROAR: A terrifying roar that drives wild Pokémon away. It is useful only in the wild.
SING: A special Normal-type technique. A soothing melody lulls the target to sleep.
SUPERSONIC: A special Normal-type technique. Supersonic sound waves are used to confuse the target.
SONICBOOM: A Normal-type attack. It inflicts a set amount of damage regardless of the target's type.
DISABLE: A technique that disables one of the target's moves. The disabled move can't be used until it wears off.
ACID: A Poison-type attack. Has a one-in-three chance of lowering the target's Defense.
EMBER: A Fire-type attack. Has a one-in-ten chance of leaving the target with a damaging burn.
FLAMETHROWER: A powerful Fire-type attack. Has a one-in-ten chance of leaving the target with a damaging burn.
MIST: Provides full protection against any enemy status attack, such as those that lower Defense.
WATER_GUN: A Water-type attack. Stronger than Bubble. Many Water-type Pokémon learn this move.
HYDRO_PUMP: The strongest Water-type attack. However, while it is powerful, it may miss the target.
SURF: A Water-type attack. The power of this technique is strong and highly accurate.
ICE_BEAM: An Ice-type attack. Has a one-in-ten chance of freezing the target solid.
BLIZZARD: The strongest Ice-type attack. Has a one-in-ten chance of freezing the target solid.
PSYBEAM: A Psychic-type attack. Has a one-in-ten of making the target confused.
BUBBLEBEAM: A Water-type attack. Stronger than Bubble. Many Water-type Pokémon learn this move.
AURORA_BEAM: An Ice-type attack. Has a one-in-three chance of reducing the target's Attack power.
HYPER_BEAM: An extremely powerful attack. The attacker becomes so tired, it has to rest the next turn.
PECK: A standard Flying-type attack. It is favored by Pokémon that have beaks and/or horns.
DRILL_PECK: A standard Flying-type attack. It is strong and highly likely to hit the target.
SUBMISSION: The strongest Fighting attack. One quarter of the damage it inflicts comes back to hurt the attacker.
LOW_KICK: A Fighting-type attack. Has a one-in-three chance of making the target flinch if it connects.
COUNTER: A retaliation move that back double the damage of a physical attack. Highly accurate.
SEISMIC_TOSS: A Fighting-type attack. Throws the target with enough force to flip the world upside down.
STRENGTH: A very powerful Normal-type attack. Also used for moving obstacles like boulders.
ABSORB: A GRASS-type attack. It adds half the HP it drained from the target to the attacker's HP.
MEGA_DRAIN: A Grass-type attack. It adds half the HP it drained from the target to the attacker's HP.
LEECH_SEED: Plants a seed on the target Pokémon. The seed slowly drains the target's HP for the attacker.
GROWTH: Raises Special to make special attacks stronger and enhance protection against special moves.
RAZOR_LEAF: A Grass-type attack that sends sharp-edged leaves at the target. Likely to get a critical hit.
SOLARBEAM: The strongest Grass-type attack. Energy is absorbed in the first turn, then fired the next turn.
POISONPOWDER: A technique that poisons the target. If poisoned, the victim loses HP steadily.
STUN_SPORE: A special move that causes paralysis. When paralyzed, the victim has a one-in-four chance of immobility.
SLEEP_POWDER: Induces sleep. A Pokémon will stay asleep for several turns if an item isn't used to wake it.
PETAL_DANCE: A dance-like attack that lasts two to three turns. Afterwards, the attacker becomes confused.
STRING_SHOT: Strings are sprayed out and wrapped around the target to reduces its Speed.
DRAGON_RAGE: A Dragon-type attack. It inflicts a set amount of damage, regardless of the target's type.
FIRE_SPIN: A Fire-type attack that lasts two to five turns. The target cannot move while surrounded by flames.
THUNDERSHOCK: An Electric-type attack. Has a one-in-ten chance of paralyzing the target.
THUNDERBOLT: An Electric-type attack. Has a one-in-ten chance of paralyzing the target.
THUNDER_WAVE: A special move that causes paralysis. When paralyzed, the victim has a one-in-four chance of immobility.
THUNDER: The strongest of all Electric-type attacks. Has a one-in-ten chance of paralyzing the target.
ROCK_THROW: A Rock-type attack. As the name implies, a huge boulder is dropped on the target.
EARTHQUAKE: An attack that inflicts the damage by shaking the ground. It is useless against Flying type Pokémon.
FISSURE: Causes a single-hit knockout if it hits. Useless against Flying-type Pokémon.
DIG: The attacker digs underground in the first turn, then pops up in the next turn to attack.
TOXIC: A technique that badly poisons the target. The amount of damage from the poison increases every turn.
CONFUSION: A Psychic-type attack. Has a one-in-ten chance of leaving the target confused.
PSYCHIC: A Psychic-type attack. Has a one-in-three chance of lowering the target's Special rating.
HYPNOSIS: A special Psychic-type move. The target is hypnotized into a deep sleep.
MEDITATE: A special technique that boosts the user's Attack power. Can normally be used up to six times.
AGILITY: A special technique that greatly boosts the user's Speed. Can normally be used up to three times.
QUICK_ATTACK: An attack that always strikes first. If both Pokémon use this, the one with higher Speed attacks first.
RAGE: A non-stop attack move. The user's Attack power increases every time it sustains damage.
TELEPORT: A special technique for instantly escaping from wild Pokémon. Useful in the wild only.
NIGHT_SHADE: A Ghost-type attack. Highly accurate, it inflicts damage regardless of the target's type.
MIMIC: A move for learning one of the opponent's moves, for use during that battle only.
SCREECH: A move that makes a horrible noise. It sharply reduces the target's Defense.
DOUBLE_TEAM: Creates illusionary copies of the user. The copies disorient the enemy, reducing its accuracy.
RECOVER: Restores HP by 1/2 of the user's maximum HP. Few Pokémon learn this technique on their own.
HARDEN: Raises the user's Defense. Useful when battling physically strong Pokémon.
MINIMIZE: Reduces the user's size and makes it harder to hit. Can normally be used up to six times.
SMOKESCREEN: Creates an obscuring cloud of smoke that reduces the enemy's accuracy.
CONFUSE_RAY: A sinister flash of light makes the target confused. A special Ghost-type technique.
WITHDRAW: Used mainly by Pokémon with shells. By withdrawing into the shell, Defense is increased.
DEFENSE_CURL: Raises the user's Defense. Can normally be used up to six times in a row.
BARRIER: Instantly forms a barrier between the user and the opponent. Defense is sharply increased.
LIGHT_SCREEN: Reduces damage from special attacks by about half. A special Psychic-type technique.
HAZE: Eliminates all changes affecting status, such as Speed and accuracy, of both Pokémon in battle.
REFLECT: Reduces damage from physical attacks by about half. A special Psychic-type technique.
FOCUS_ENERGY: Raises the likelihood of nailing the opponent's weak spot for a critical hit.
BIDE: The user waits for several turns. At the end, it returns double the damage it received.
METRONOME: The user waggles its finger, triggering a move. There is no telling what will happen.
MIRROR_MOVE: A move that strikes back with the opponent's last move. This move comes after the enemy's move.
SELFDESTRUCT: The user explodes, inflicting damage on the enemy, then faints. Useless against Ghost-type.
EGG_BOMB: A Normal-type attack. An egg is launched at the target. It may miss, however.
LICK: A Ghost-type attack. Has a one-in-three chance of leaving the target with paralysis.
SMOG: Smog is spewed as a cloud. Has a fifty-fifty chance of poisoning the target.
SLUDGE: A Poison-type attack. Has a fifty-fifty chance of poisoning the target.
BONE_CLUB: A physical attack using a bone as a club. If it connects, it may cause the target to flinch.
FIRE_BLAST: The strongest Fire-type attack. Has a one-in-three chance of inflicting a burn on the target.
WATERFALL: The target is hit with a blow packing the power of fish traveling up waterfalls.
CLAMP: The target is gripped in the attacker's shell for two to five turns. It can't move while under the attack.
SWIFT: A Normal-type attack. It is highly accurate, so it can be counted on to inflict damage.
SKULL_BASH: In the first turn, the attacker tucks in its head. The next turn, it head-butts at full steam.
SPIKE_CANNON: A physical attack consisting of two to five consecutive hits. Highly accurate.
CONSTRICT: A Normal-type attack. Has a one-in-three chance of reducing the target's Speed.
AMNESIA: Sharply raises the user's Special stat. Also increases protection against special attacks.
KINESIS: A special move of bending spoons to confound the enemy. Makes the user harder to hit.
SOFTBOILED: Restores HP by 1/2 of the user's maximum HP. May also be used in the field.
HI_JUMP_KICK: Stronger than a Jump Kick. If it misses, the attacker sustains 1/8 damage it should have caused.
GLARE: The target is transfixed with terrifying sharp eyes. The target is frightened into paralysis.
DREAM_EATER: Works only on sleeping Pokémon. This technique steals the target's HP and adds it to the user's HP.
POISON_GAS: A poisonous cloud of gas is forcefully expelled to poison the target.
BARRAGE: Several spheres are thrown consecutively at the target to inflict damage.
LEECH_LIFE: An HP-draining attack. It adds half the HP it drained from the target to the attacker's HP.
LOVELY_KISS: A special move that puts the target to sleep with a big kiss. (Actually, the victim passes out.)
SKY_ATTACK: The strongest Flying-type attack. Energy is stored in the first turn, then fired the next turn.
TRANSFORM: Transforms the user into a copy of the target, including the type. All moves have only five PP each.
BUBBLE: A Water-type attack. Has a one-in-three chance of reducing the target's Speed.
DIZZY_PUNCH: A Normal-type attack. The punch is relatively strong and highly accurate.
SPORE: Special spores are scattered from mushrooms. If the opponent inhales the spores, it will fall asleep.
FLASH: Creates a brilliant flash of light that blinds the target. This technique reduces the opponent's accuracy.
PSYWAVE: A Psychic-type attack of varying intensity. It occasionally inflicts heavy damage.
SPLASH: A move that involves only flopping and Splashing around in front of the opponent. It has no effect.
ACID_ARMOR: Melts the user's body for protection. A move that sharply raises Defense.
CRABHAMMER: A move that is used only by Pokémon with pincers. Likely to get a critical hit.
EXPLOSION: The most powerful attack of all. However, the attacker faints after using this move.
FURY_SWIPES: The target is scratched by sharp claws two to five times in quick succession.
BONEMERANG: A boomerang made of bone is thrown to inflict damage twice -- on the way out and on its return.
REST: The user takes a nap to fully restore its HP and recover from any status abnormalities.
ROCK_SLIDE: A Rock-type attack that hits the target with an avalanche of rocks and boulders.
HYPER_FANG: A Normal-type attack. Has a one-in-ten chance of making the target flinch.
SHARPEN: Raises the user's Attack power. The edges of the Pokémon are made harder for more impact.
CONVERSION: A special move that switches the user's elemental type to that of the target.
TRI_ATTACK: A Normal-type attack. A triangular field of energy is created and launched at the target.
SUPER_FANG: If it hits, this attack cuts the target's HP in half. Learned by Pokémon with developed fangs.
SLASH: A Normal-type attack. It has a high probability of a critical hit for inflicting double the damage.
SUBSTITUTE: Uses 1/4 of the user's maximum HP to create a substitute that takes the opponent's attacks.
STRUGGLE: Used only if the user runs totally out of PP. The user is hit with 1/4 of the damage it inflicts.
